description:
Your sail boat proudly cuts through the waters of the caribbean, carrying you closer to the many treasures marked on your old map. Suddenly you hear the dreadful sound of crashing wood. The razor-sharp reefs tore a menacing hole into the hull of your boat. But as a true salty sailor, there's no giving up! Can you find all the treasure while keeping your leaky boat afloat?

Leaky Boat is a real-time solitaire game (free to print n' play), where you are constantly up to your neck in watery peril. You frantically roll your dice to navigate through dangerous waters and to collect the riches buried on faraway islands. A unique sandtimer-mechanism simulates the treasure chests weighing you down and the salty waters continuously pouring into your boat as you struggle to stay afloat.

&ldquo;Just a few big treasures and then I&rsquo;ll stop&rdquo; you say to yourself as you sail towards the horizon, your boat circled by hungry sharks&hellip;

This 36-card Kaijuu Expansion Deck contains Monsters and words relevant to their lifestyle, such as &ldquo;Radioactive,&rdquo; &ldquo;Beasts,&rdquo; &ldquo;Devour,&rdquo; and &ldquo;Tokyo.&rdquo;

Each expansion to Japanese: The Game adds new vocabulary words, and thus the rules that go along with how each noun, verb, or particle can be placed to make a sentence.

The expansion decks are shuffled in with the main deck to accommodate more players (the game plays 2 by itself and needs either an additional core deck or an expansion to accommodate more), or just to add less common words to the mix for 1-2 players.

This game is the Napoleonic battle of river Trebbia (june 1799). Wise Bayonets uses the same rules system of Mass&eacute;na at Loano, integrated with rules needed to reflect the different battle terrain and tactical situation. Compared to the previous game much more emphasis is given to cavalry and much less to the formation of tirailleurs (almost useless in the plain between rivers Tidone, Trebbia and Po).

Components:

    One game-map 84x60 cm; 
    216 5/8&rdquo; and 140 1/2&rdquo; die cut counters; 
    Three Player Aid Cards; 
    Rule booklet with scenarios and an historical commentary 


Scale:

    1 turn: 1 hour; 
    1 hex: 300 m (about 328 yards); 
    1 strength point: 2-300 men for infantry, 150-200 for the cavalry or 2-3 guns


(from publisher's website)

Yin-Yang is a brief abstrat game for two players, each player takes both of the white and the black stones for playing. They take turns placing stones on the 5x5 game board, for the purpose of making a square by four stones in the same color. 
In the game, each player belongs to Yin or Yang side. So does the square been made on the board. The player who&rsquo;s Yin-Yang is the same as the square wins the game.

On which the Yin-Yang of a square depends:
White stone is Yang; 
Black stone is Yin;
Odd number of lines of gribs the square covered is Yang;
Even number of lines of gribs the square covered is Yin;

Combining Yin-Yang of the stones with the size of the square just as  multiplication rules of plus and minus, the result is the Yin-Yang of the square:
White stone x Odd number = Yang
White stone x Even number = Yin
Black stone x Odd number = Yin
Black stone x Even number =Yang

Objective: sink most boats with 5 torpedoes
-    acting by turns &ndash;

4 ships are positioned at an agreed distance;
An elastic band is stretched and a &lsquo;wooden&rsquo; torpedo is loaded; each player has 5 shots to hit as many boats as possible;  aim and unleash &ndash; after you&rsquo;ve made 5 shots it&rsquo;s next player&rsquo;s turn.

